DefaultTranslation.Text: Following condition required before ready to start:

Signal Fault Conveyor Position. Sensor located in black box under crib number two, under the line laser. If Message for Fuse 4.3 also pops up, check fuse and wet/loose connectors. IF NOT - Faulty sensor. Check if sensor has lights or connector is loose. Temporarily connect new sensor by the connector to troubleshoot if the cable has power. Change sensor if new sensor has lights.

Signal Fault Neck Height Arm Sensor. If Message for Fuse 4.3 also pops up, check fuse and wet/loose connectors. IF NOT - Faulty sensor. Check if sensor has lights or connector is loose. Temporarily connect new sensor by the connector to troubleshoot if the cable has power. Change sensor if new sensor has lights. You can bypass this problem by disabling headcutting.
Signal Fault Fish Height Measuring Lasers. Visually check the lasers have power on, and wave your hand under the lasers to initialize them after a power up. Check fuse and connector.
Signal Fault Head Saw Position. Has fuse F6 blown? Replace with a 10A glassfuse in Folla's main electric cabinet. If fuse blows immediately again, check for damage and contact maintenance.
Startfail / Timeout. Check conveyor, headscrew or belly screw is blocked or not home. If Start button does not reset machine, try manually controlling it and press run home in the manual controls.
Safety Doors Opened. Check yellow arrow for which door. Please close the doors on Folla for continued use.

Position Error Belly Screw. If repeated errors, check inductive sensor at the right side of the belly screw. Reset its position at the page "Encoder". Modes & Settings > Sensors > Encoder. Contact maintenance.

Position Error Head Grip Screw. If repeated errors, check inductive sensor at the side of the headgrip. Reset its position at the page "Encoder". Modes & Settings > Sensors > Encoder. Contact maintenance.
Position Error Belly Actuator. Can happen after turning on main power on machine. Press start.
Air Press Alarm. Start Air Compressor. Check for air leakage.

Drive Fault Conveyor. PRESS START TO RESET. Check for blockage, check for fish stuck under machine. Unjam fish/cribs before trying to move conveyor. If Start button does not reset machine, try manually controlling it and press run home in the manual controls. Read Additional Information if problem does not reset.

Drive Fault Belly Saw. PRESS START TO RESET. Check for blockage. If Start button does not reset machine, try manually controlling it and press run home in the manual controls. Read Additional Information if problem does not reset.

Drive Fault Belly Screw. PRESS START TO RESET. Check for blockage. If Start button does not reset machine, try manually controlling it and press run home in the manual controls. Read Additional Information if problem does not reset.

Drive Fault Head Saw. PRESS START TO RESET. Check for heads blocking around the saw. If Start button does not reset machine, try manually controlling it and press run in the manual controls. Read Additional Information if problem does not reset.

Drive Fault Head Screw. PRESS START TO RESET. Check for blockage. If Start button does not reset machine, try manually controlling it and press run in the manual controls. Read Additional Information if problem does not reset.
U25 Driver Error. PRESS START TO RESET. Check for blockage. If Start button does not reset machine, try manually controlling it and press run home in the manual controls.
Y35 Head Actuator Error. Check for blockage. If Start button does not reset machine, try manually controlling it up and down. Check status light on the plug of actuator and contact maintenance.

Fuse 4.3 for Neck Height Sensor And Conveyor Positioning Sensor is blown. Replace with a 1A glassfuse in Folla's main electric cabinet. If fuse blows immediately again, check for damage and contact maintenance.

Fuse 4.4 for Proximity Sensors on conveyor and head screw is blown. Replace with a 1A glassfuse in Folla's main electric cabinet. If fuse blows immediately again, check for damage and contact maintenance.
Fuse 4.5 for Proximity Sensors on Belly system is blown. Replace with a 1A glassfuse in Folla's main electric cabinet. If fuse blows immediately again, check for damage and contact maintenance.

Fuse 4.6 for Operator Buttons, Air Sensors and Signals Out PLC is blown. Replace with a 1A glassfuse in Folla's main electric cabinet. If fuse blows immediately again, check for damage and contact maintenance.
Ground Fault in the 24V system has been detected. Check for water-damaged sensors or cable connectors. Fuses has possibly blown. Did this happend after machine has been washed? Contact maintenance.
